article.headline: Texas-San Antonio 80, McMurry 55
article.story: SAN ANTONIO -- Devin Gibson scored 14 points and Omar Johnson added 13 to lead Texas-San Antonio to a 80-55 win over McMurry. Texas-San Antonio (2-2) benefited from sloppy play in the game, outscoring McMurry 32-6 in points off turnovers. The Roadrunners also outscored McMurry (0-1) in second chance opportunities, 12-9. Johnson made three 3-pointers while Gibson made two for Texas-San Antonio. Jonathan Walker was the only player to score in double digits for McMurry (0-1). He had some defensive help from Brett Johnson who grabbed 8 defensive rebounds and 12 overall in the game.
